1
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:05,881
-What's happened?
-The time vortex. It's gone.

2
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:07,799
Well, we've landed.
We've got to be somewhere.

3
00:00:07,883 --> 00:00:10,511
It's parallel, right? Like a parallel Earth
only they've got zeppelins?

4
00:00:10,594 --> 00:00:11,762
Am I right? I'm right, aren't I?

5
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:13,931
A parallel world where my dad's still alive.

6
00:00:14,056 --> 00:00:16,975
DOCTOR: Rose, he's not your father
and she is not your mother.

7
00:00:17,059 --> 00:00:19,019
What's that? Mickey, we've got power!

8
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:21,021
You're a fine businessman, John.

9
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,814
But you're not God.

10
00:00:22,898 --> 00:00:24,816
What am I doing there?

11
00:00:24,942 --> 00:00:28,487
He doesn't just look like me.
He is exactly the same.

12
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,614
-ROSE: What are they?
-Cybermen.

13
00:00:32,950 --> 00:00:33,992
Come on!

14
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:45,128
There's no need to damage us.
We're good stock.

15
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:49,508
We volunteer for the upgrade programme.
Take us to be processed.

16
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:51,593
You are rogue elements.

17
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:52,761
But we surrender.

18
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:54,930
You are incompatible.

19
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,431
But this is a surrender!

20
00:00:56,515 --> 00:00:58,600
You will be deleted.

21
00:00:58,976 --> 00:01:01,061
But we're surrendering!
Listen to me! We surrender!

22
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,980
You are inferior.

23
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:05,691
Man will be reborn as Cyberman

24
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:09,820
but you will perish under maximum deletion.

25
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:13,824
Delete. Delete. Delete.

26
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,868
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

27
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:01,330
-What the hell was that?
-Or how about instead, run!

28
00:02:02,164 --> 00:02:04,082
(HORN HONKING)

29
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:08,045
Everybody in!

30
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:14,676
-I've got to go back. My wife's in there.
-Anyone inside that house is dead.

31
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,762
If you want to help,
then don't let her die for nothing.

32
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:19,014
You've got to come with us right now.

33
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:21,224
Come on, get a move on.

34
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:23,060
Rose, she's not your mother.

35
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,811
-I know.
-Come on.

36
00:02:26,313 --> 00:02:30,108
Finished chatting?
Never seen a slower getaway in my life!

37
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:50,128
What was that thing?

38
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:52,547
Little bit of technology from my home.

39
00:02:52,631 --> 00:02:54,007
It's stopped glowing. Has it run out?

40
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:57,427
It's on a revitalising loop.
It'll charge back up in about four hours.

41
00:02:57,511 --> 00:03:00,263
-So we don't have a weapon anymore?
-Yeah, we've got weapons.

42
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:03,642
Might not work on those metal things
but they're good enough for men like him.

43
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,769
Leave him alone! What's he done wrong?

44
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:08,105
Oh, you know, just laid a trap
that's wiped out the government

45
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:09,690
and left Lumic in charge.

46
00:03:09,773 --> 00:03:12,567
If I was part of all that,
do you think I'd leave my wife inside?

47
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:16,071
Maybe your plan went wrong.
Still gives us the right to execute you, though.

48
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:18,156
Talk about executions,
you'll make me your enemy.

49
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:20,367
And take some really good advice,
you don't want to do that.

50
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:23,620
All the same, we have evidence
that says Pete Tyler's been working

51
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:25,997
for the Lumic since 20.5.

52
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,669
Is that true?

53
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:33,797
Tell them, Mrs M.

54
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,967
We've got a government mole
who feeds us information.

55
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:40,971
Lumic's private files,
his South American operations, the lot.

56
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:43,390
Secret broadcasts twice a week.

57
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:46,143
-Broadcasts from Gemini?
-And how do you know that?

58
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,602
I'm Gemini! That's me!

59
00:03:47,686 --> 00:03:52,274
-RICKY: Yeah, well, you would say that.
-Encrypted wavelength 657, using binary 9.

60
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:56,737
That's the only reason I was working for Lumic,
to get information.

61
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:59,573
I thought I was broadcasting
to the security services. What do I get?

62
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:02,951
Scooby Doo and his gang.
They've even got the van.

63
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:05,162
No, no, but the Preachers
know what they're doing.

64
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:06,997
Ricky said he's London's most wanted.

65
00:04:07,122 --> 00:04:08,999
Yeah, that's not exactly...

66
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:10,709
Not exactly what?

67
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:13,879
I'm London's most wanted for parking tickets.

68
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,548
Great.

69
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:18,508
They were deliberate. I was fighting the system.

70
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:21,678
-Park anywhere, that's me.
-Good policy. I do much the same.

71
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:24,723
I'm the Doctor by the way, if anyone's interested.

72
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:26,308
And I'm Rose. Hello.

73
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:28,268
Even better. That's the name of my dog.

74
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:31,521
Still, at least I've got the catering staff
on my side.

75
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:34,357
I knew you weren't a traitor.

76
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:35,901
Why's that, then?

77
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:39,446
I just did.

78
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:42,866
They took my wife.

79
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,284
She might still be alive.

80
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:48,747
That's even worse 'cause that's what Lumic does.

81
00:04:48,872 --> 00:04:52,709
He takes the living
and he turns them into those machines.

82
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:54,669
Cybermen.

83
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:57,214
They're called Cybermen.

84
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:00,050
And I'd take those Ear Pods off if I were you.

85
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:03,303
You never know, Lumic could be listening.

86
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,680
But he's over-reached himself.
He's still just a businessman.

87
00:05:05,764 --> 00:05:07,098
He's assassinated the President.

88
00:05:07,182 --> 00:05:10,060
All we need to do is get to the city
and inform the authorities.

89
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,646
Because I promise you, this ends tonight.

90
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:19,152
LUMIC: My everlasting children.
Tell me, how does it feel?

91
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:20,904
We feel nothing.

92
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:23,657
But in your mind, what do you think?

93
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,868
We think the same. We are uniform.

94
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:30,121
But you think of what?

95
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:34,751
We think of the humans.
We think of their difference and their pain.

96
00:05:34,918 --> 00:05:38,880
They suffer in the skin. They must be upgraded.

97
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:42,425
Excellent. Then let's begin.

98
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:45,762
Computer, identify John Lumic.

99
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:48,056
COMPUTER: Voice print acknowledged.

100
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,976
Activate Ear Pod primary sequence.

101
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:53,562
Please state area of activation.

102
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,397
The city of London.

103
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,441
I've just declared independence.

104
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:00,735
Begin transmission.

105
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,703
(EAR PODS BEEPING)

106
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:26,553
LUMIC: 7hey will come to me. My new children.

107
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:28,638
The immortal ones.

108
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,057
The whole of London has been sealed off.

109
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:34,269
There are reports of an army,
an army of metal men.

110
00:06:34,352 --> 00:06:38,648
All citizens should remove their Ear Pods.
I repeat, remove all Ear Pods.

111
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,567
London has been placed under martial law.

112
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:44,821
If you are hearing this, stay in your homes.
I repeat, stay in your homes.

113
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:46,948
(GRUNTING)

114
00:06:47,032 --> 00:06:48,783
(LOUD BUZZING)

115
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:51,202
Oh, no, you don't.

116
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:55,457
MRS MOORE: What the hell?
ROSE: What's going on?

117
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:58,001
It's the Ear Pods. Lumic's taken control.

118
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:00,170
Can't we just, I don't know, take them off?

119
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:03,715
Don't. It'll cause a brainstorm.

120
00:07:04,174 --> 00:07:08,011
The human race, for such an intelligent lot,
you aren't half susceptible.

121
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,597
Give anyone a chance to take control
and you submit.

122
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,266
Sometimes I think you like it. Easy life.

123
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:15,644
Hey. Come and see.

124
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:25,278
ROSE: Where are they all going?
DOCTOR: I don't know.

125
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,155
Lumic must have a base of operations.

126
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:31,076
Battersea. That's where he was
building his prototypes.

127
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:32,619
Why's he doing it?

128
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:34,204
He's dying.

129
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:38,208
This all started out as a way of
prolonging life, keeping the brain alive.

130
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,542
At any cost.

131
00:07:39,668 --> 00:07:42,087
Thing is, I've seen Cybermen before, haven't I?

132
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,923
The head, those handle shapes,
in Van Statten's Museum.

133
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:47,050
Oh, there are Cybermen in our universe.

134
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,887
They started on an ordinary world just like this,
then swarmed across the galaxy.

135
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:53,974
This lot are a parallel version.
They're starting from scratch here on Earth.

136
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:56,184
What the hell are you two on about?

137
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,895
Never mind.
Come on, we need to get out of the city.

138
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:01,022
Okay, split up. Mrs Moore, you look after that lot.

139
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:05,735
Jake, distract them, go right, I'll go left.
We'll meet back at Bridge Street. Move.

140
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:08,238
I'm going with him.

141
00:08:09,072 --> 00:08:10,865
Come on. Let's go.

142
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,579
DOCTOR: Back!

143
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:33,513
-Which way? I don't know where we are.
-Did they see us?

144
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,348
-Do they know where we are?
-I bet they saw us.

145
00:08:35,432 --> 00:08:37,225
I bet they saw us in the dark.

146
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:38,893
-They know where we are.
-They know where we are.

147
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:42,939
I don't get it. What is it with you?
You are exactly like me.

148
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:46,443
-I don't know. I reckon you're braver.
-Oh, yeah. Ten times.

149
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:48,278
Still, your friends aren't bad, I'll give you that.

150
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:51,448
Oh, that's the Doctor and Rose.
I just tag along behind.

151
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:53,658
Well, then you're not that bad.

152
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:56,327
-Do you think?
-Yeah, suppose.

153
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:57,954
(STOMPING)

154
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:01,291
Cybermen.

155
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,626
-Split up!
-Split up!

156
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,706
(WHISPERING) Go.

157
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:54,594
TANNOY: Chamber 12 now closed for sterilisation.

158
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:59,766
All reject stock will be incinerated.

159
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:21,412
Come on! Come on!

160
00:10:22,205 --> 00:10:23,248
Come on!

161
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,543
No!

162
00:10:43,852 --> 00:10:46,312
QYBERMAN: This one is un-programmed.

163
00:10:46,563 --> 00:10:49,732
Mr Crane, I thought you were one of the faithful.

164
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:53,570
Oh, that I am, sir.
My Ear Pod must have malfunctioned,

165
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,488
for which I apologise.

166
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:57,907
If I might?

167
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:03,746
I'd like to request an upgrade, sir.

168
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:07,417
I've seen the future
and it's copyright Cybus Industries.

169
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,626
Sign me up.

170
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:10,503
A willing volunteer?

171
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,714
You've known me a long time, sir.

172
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:16,467
Quite a team, you and me.
I've been with you all the way.

173
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:22,390
But believe me, sir,
knowing you so well, I know exactly what to do.

174
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,101
No!

175
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:29,772
No! Help me!

176
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,943
Die, you...

177
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:40,366
-Help me!
-You are in pain. We can remove pain forever.

178
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:44,204
No. Not yet. I'm not ready.

179
00:11:44,287 --> 00:11:46,623
We will give you immortality.

180
00:11:46,748 --> 00:11:52,587
I've told you,
I will upgrade only with my last breath.

181
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,797
Then breathe no more.

182
00:11:57,175 --> 00:12:00,803
No. No. I command you. No!

183
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:02,972
(GASPING)

184
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:08,645
I ran past the river, you should've seen it.
The whole city's on the march.

185
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:11,147
Hundreds of Cybermen, all down the Thames.

186
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:13,858
Here he is.

187
00:12:16,653 --> 00:12:19,989
-Which one are you?
-I'm sorry, the Cybermen, he couldn't...

188
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:21,574
Are you Ricky?

189
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,785
Are you Ricky?

190
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:26,246
Mickey, that's you, isn't it?

191
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:27,413
Yeah.

192
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:34,837
He tried. He was running.
There was too many of them.

193
00:12:34,963 --> 00:12:36,589
Shut it.

194
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:40,176
-There was nothing I could do.
-I said just shut it!

195
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,428
Don't even talk about him.

196
00:12:42,512 --> 00:12:44,305
You're nothing, you are.

197
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:48,059
Nothing.

198
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:51,980
We can mourn him when London is safe.

199
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:55,108
For now, we move on.

200
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:19,882
The whole of London's been sealed off

201
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:23,469
and the entire population's
been taken inside that place.

202
00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:25,847
To be converted.

203
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,391
We've got to get in there and shut it down.

204
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:31,728
-How do we do that?
-Oh, I'll think of something.

205
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:35,398
-You're just making this up as you go along.
-Yep.

206
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:37,358
But I do it brilliantly.

207
00:13:39,986 --> 00:13:42,947
MRS MOORE: That's a schematic
of the old factory.

208
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:48,369
Look, cooling tunnels underneath the plant
big enough to walk through.

209
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:50,997
We go under then up into the control centre.

210
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:55,293
There's another way in. Through the front door.

211
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:58,296
If they've taken Jackie for upgrading,
that's how she'll get in.

212
00:13:58,379 --> 00:14:00,673
We can't just go strolling up.

213
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:04,302
Well, we could, with these.

214
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:08,348
Fake Ear Pods. Dead, no signal.

215
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,601
But put them on, the Cybermen
would mistake you for one of the crowd.

216
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:13,144
Then that's my job.

217
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:16,773
You'd have to show no emotion, none at all.
Any sign of emotion would give you away.

218
00:14:16,898 --> 00:14:19,484
-How many of those have you got?
-Just two sets.

219
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,152
Okay.

220
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:24,155
If that's the best way of finding Jackie,

221
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,282
then I'm coming with you.

222
00:14:26,366 --> 00:14:28,785
-Why does she matter to you?
-We haven't got time.

223
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:31,204
Doctor, I'm going with him and that's that.

224
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,414
-No stopping you, is there?
-Nope.

225
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:38,753
Tell you what,
we can attack the Ear Pods at the same time.

226
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:42,757
Give people their minds back
so they don't walk into that place like sheep.

227
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,300
Jakey-boy.

228
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:51,557
Lumic's transmitting the control signal.
It must be from over there.

229
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:53,476
(BEEPING)

230
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,938
There it is. On the zeppelin, do you see?

231
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,898
Great big transmitter.

232
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:03,069
Good thing Lumic likes showing off.
Reckon you can take it out?

233
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,862
Consider it done.

234
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:09,826
Mrs Moore, would you care to
accompany me into the cooling tunnels?

235
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,537
How could I refuse an offer of cooling tunnels?

236
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,039
We attack on three sides. Above, between, below.

237
00:15:15,123 --> 00:15:17,500
We get to the control centre,
we stop the conversion machines.

238
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,419
What about me?

239
00:15:19,502 --> 00:15:22,588
Mickey, you can, um...

240
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:25,425
What? Stay out of trouble? Be the tin dog?

241
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:29,011
No, those days are over. I'm going with Jake.

242
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:31,639
-JAKE: I don't need you, idiot.
-I'm not an idiot!

243
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:35,226
You got that? I'm offering to help.

244
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,729
Whatever.

245
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:42,984
Mickey.

246
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:45,528
Good luck.

247
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:47,029
Yeah. You, too.

248
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,949
-Rose, I'll see you later.
-Yeah, you'd better.

249
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:53,077
If we survive this, I'll see you back at the Tardis.

250
00:15:57,123 --> 00:15:58,499
That's a promise.

251
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:06,507
Good luck.

252
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:24,734
It's freezing.

253
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,820
Any sign of a light switch?

254
00:16:27,904 --> 00:16:31,616
Can't see a thing. But I've got these.

255
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:34,035
-A device for every occasion.
-Ooh.

256
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,578
Put it on.

257
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:40,750
Haven't got a hot dog in there, have you?
I'm starving.

258
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:44,462
Of all the things to wish for.
That's mechanically recovered meat.

259
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:47,924
I know. It's the Cyberman of food, but it's tasty.

260
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:51,427
A proper torch as well.

261
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:53,638
Let's see where we are.

262
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,977
Already converted, just put on ice.

263
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,605
Come on.

264
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,408
DOCTOR: Let's go slowly.

265
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,123
Keep an eye out for trip systems.

266
00:17:42,103 --> 00:17:46,607
TANNOY: Chamber 6 now open
for human upgrading.

267
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:52,238
Chamber 7 now open for human upgrading.

268
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:59,287
Chamber 8 now open for human upgrading.

269
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:02,498
Just put them on. Don't show any emotion.

270
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:04,667
No signs, nothing, okay?

271
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:07,003
Don't worry. We can do it.

272
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:10,631
We could die in there. Why are you doing this?

273
00:18:10,715 --> 00:18:13,134
Let's just say I'm doing it for my mum and dad.

274
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:15,886
Right, let's go.

275
00:18:17,847 --> 00:18:22,435
Chamber 8 now open for human upgrading.

276
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:28,316
Chamber 9 now open for human upgrading.

277
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:33,404
Chamber 10 now open for human upgrading.

278
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:43,581
Chamber 11 now open for human upgrading.

279
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:20,618
Two guards. We can take them.

280
00:19:20,743 --> 00:19:23,913
-Don't kill them.
-Who put you in charge?

281
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:27,875
If you kill them, what's the difference
between you and a Cyberman?

282
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:30,961
Well, I suppose we could use these.

283
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,590
Smelling salts?

284
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:37,885
Bit stronger than that.
One of Mrs Moore's little tricks.

285
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:39,929
Should knock them out.

286
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:42,390
(WHISPERING) Three, two, one.

287
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:59,073
There's gotta be more guards on board.

288
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:02,118
Then let's go get them.

289
00:20:06,956 --> 00:20:11,127
DOCTOR: How did you get into this, then?
Rattling along with the Preachers?

290
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:14,255
MRS MOORE: Oh, I used to be ordinary.

291
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:18,843
Worked at Cybus Industries, 9-to-5.

292
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:22,513
Until one day,
I find something I'm not supposed to.

293
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:24,890
A file on the mainframe.

294
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:27,643
All I did was read it.

295
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:32,690
Then suddenly, I've got men with guns
knocking in the middle of the night.

296
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:35,192
A life on the run.

297
00:20:36,152 --> 00:20:38,154
Then I found the Preachers.

298
00:20:38,738 --> 00:20:43,826
They needed a techie, so I just sat down
and taught myself everything.

299
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,995
What about Mr Moore?

300
00:20:46,162 --> 00:20:48,247
Well, he's not called Moore.

301
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:51,667
I got that from a book.

302
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:53,085
Mrs Moore.

303
00:20:54,295 --> 00:20:56,505
It's safer not to use real names.

304
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,050
But he thinks I'm dead.

305
00:21:00,843 --> 00:21:03,179
It was the only way to keep him safe.

306
00:21:03,304 --> 00:21:04,680
Him and the kids.

307
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:10,227
What about you? Got any family or...

308
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:14,398
Oh, who needs family?
I've got the whole world on my shoulders.

309
00:21:15,149 --> 00:21:16,901
Go on, then.

310
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:18,694
What's your real name?

311
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,197
Angela Price.

312
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:23,741
Don't tell a soul.

313
00:21:24,492 --> 00:21:25,868
Not a word.

314
00:21:30,206 --> 00:21:31,624
(BEEPING)

315
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:40,758
Movement in Deepcold 6.

316
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,594
Awaken the army.

317
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:48,891
Doctor, did that one just move?

318
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:51,727
It's just the torchlight.

319
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:53,395
Keep going, come on.

320
00:21:53,896 --> 00:21:55,648
They're waking up. Run!

321
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:12,331
MRS MOORE: Get up! Quick! They're coming!

322
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,251
Open it! Open it!

323
00:22:16,252 --> 00:22:19,255
Get up! Quick, quick!

324
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,257
Come on!

325
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:30,850
Oh, good team, Mrs Moore.

326
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:38,774
TANNOY: Units upgraded now 6,500.

327
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:43,487
Repeat, 6,500 and rising.

328
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:51,662
You will wait.

329
00:22:54,123 --> 00:22:55,457
You okay?

330
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:57,751
No.

331
00:22:57,835 --> 00:23:02,298
TANNOY: Chamber 6 now open
for human upgrading.

332
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:08,971
All reject stock will be incinerated.

333
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:47,176
Any sign of Jackie?

334
00:23:50,721 --> 00:23:55,351
You are Peter Tyler. Confirm. You are Peter Tyler.

335
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:57,519
Confirm.

336
00:23:57,603 --> 00:24:02,691
I recognise you. I went first.
My name was Jacqueline Tyler.

337
00:24:02,775 --> 00:24:04,193
-No.
-What?

338
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:06,695
They are un-programmed, restrain.

339
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:10,074
You're lying, you're not her. You're not my Jackie.

340
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:14,912
Now I am Cyberform. Once I was Jacqueline Tyler.

341
00:24:15,371 --> 00:24:18,624
But you can't be. Not her.

342
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:21,460
Her brain is inside this body.

343
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:23,462
Jacks, I came to save you.

344
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:27,967
This man worked with Cybus Industries
to create our species.

345
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:33,097
He will be rewarded, by force.
Take them to Cyber Control.

346
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:39,603
They killed her. They took her and killed her.

347
00:24:39,687 --> 00:24:42,731
Maybe there's a chance, I don't know.
Maybe we can reverse it.

348
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:44,441
There's nothing we can do.

349
00:24:44,525 --> 00:24:46,694
But if she remembers...

350
00:24:49,029 --> 00:24:52,491
Where is she? Which one was it?
Which one was her?

351
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:56,161
They all look the same.

352
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:04,086
Nice one, nobody's home.
Find the transmitter controls.

353
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:05,796
-What do they look like?
-I don't know.

354
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:10,217
They might have "transmitter controls”
written in big red letters. Just look.

355
00:25:16,807 --> 00:25:18,267
Cyberman!

356
00:25:37,161 --> 00:25:38,537
It's dead.

357
00:25:40,122 --> 00:25:42,207
I don't think it was ever alive.

358
00:25:46,837 --> 00:25:50,299
It's empty, no brain. It's just a robot suit.
It's for display.

359
00:25:51,717 --> 00:25:53,135
Okay.

360
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,179
Transmitter.

361
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:06,648
You are not upgraded.

362
00:26:06,732 --> 00:26:09,610
Yeah, well, upgrade this.

363
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:21,163
-What the hell was that thing?
-Electromagnetic bomb.

364
00:26:22,081 --> 00:26:25,167
Takes out computers.
I figured it might stop a Cyber suit.

365
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:29,505
Well, you figured right.
Now, let's have a look. Know your enemy.

366
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:32,299
Got a logo on the front.

367
00:26:33,050 --> 00:26:35,010
Lumic's turned them into a brand.

368
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:39,515
Heart of steel.

369
00:26:42,392 --> 00:26:43,602
But look.

370
00:26:46,355 --> 00:26:48,857
-Is that flesh?
-Hmm.

371
00:26:49,691 --> 00:26:51,443
A central nervous system.

372
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:55,114
Artificially grown then threaded throughout
the suit so it responds like a living thing.

373
00:26:55,197 --> 00:26:57,908
Well, it is a living thing.

374
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,369
Oh, but look.

375
00:27:01,829 --> 00:27:05,916
Emotional inhibitor. Stops them feeling anything.

376
00:27:06,041 --> 00:27:07,543
But why?

377
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:12,422
It's still got a human brain.
Imagine its reaction if it could see itself.

378
00:27:12,548 --> 00:27:14,716
Realise itself inside this thing.

379
00:27:15,551 --> 00:27:17,386
It would go insane.

380
00:27:18,554 --> 00:27:21,974
So they cut out the one thing
that makes them human.

381
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:23,851
Because they have to.

382
00:27:23,934 --> 00:27:27,020
Why am I cold?

383
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:29,064
Oh, my God, it's alive.

384
00:27:29,815 --> 00:27:34,111
-It can feel.
-We broke the inhibitor. I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

385
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:36,530
Why so cold?

386
00:27:36,613 --> 00:27:38,282
Can you remember your name?

387
00:27:38,365 --> 00:27:41,743
Sally. Sally Phelan.

388
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:43,537
You're a woman.

389
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:45,539
Where's Gareth?

390
00:27:46,415 --> 00:27:47,749
Who's Gareth?

391
00:27:47,833 --> 00:27:49,668
He can't see me.

392
00:27:49,918 --> 00:27:53,714
It's unlucky the night before.

393
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:56,383
You're getting married?

394
00:27:56,466 --> 00:28:00,888
I'm cold. I'm so cold.

395
00:28:02,014 --> 00:28:03,682
It's all right.

396
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:07,853
You sleep now, Sally. Just go to sleep.

397
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:15,235
Sally Phelan didn't die for nothing.

398
00:28:15,861 --> 00:28:19,573
'Cause that's the key, the emotional inhibitor.

399
00:28:19,656 --> 00:28:22,117
If we could find the code behind it,
the cancellation code,

400
00:28:22,201 --> 00:28:24,912
then feed it throughout the system
into every Cyberman's head,

401
00:28:24,995 --> 00:28:27,164
they'd realise what they are.

402
00:28:27,247 --> 00:28:28,957
And what happens then?

403
00:28:29,625 --> 00:28:31,460
I think it would kill them.

404
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:36,632
-Can we do that?
-We've got to.

405
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:39,593
Before they kill everyone else.

406
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:42,262
There's no choice, Doctor.

407
00:28:42,346 --> 00:28:44,264
It's got to be done.

408
00:28:51,647 --> 00:28:54,608
No! No! You didn't have to kill her!

409
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:57,986
Sensors detect a binary vascular system.

410
00:28:58,070 --> 00:29:03,283
You are an unknown upgrade.
You will be taken for analysis.

411
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:15,963
The transmitter controls are sealed behind here.
We need oxyacetylene or something.

412
00:29:16,046 --> 00:29:17,839
Oh, and I forgot to bring it with me.

413
00:29:17,923 --> 00:29:20,300
-Then what do we do?
-We'll crash the zeppelin.

414
00:29:20,384 --> 00:29:24,137
-With us inside it?
-We could set it on automatic and then just leq it.

415
00:29:24,221 --> 00:29:25,681
Let's have a look.

416
00:29:31,353 --> 00:29:34,690
It's locked. There's got to be an override.

417
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:37,776
Let me have a go.
I'm good with computers. Trust me.

418
00:29:58,171 --> 00:30:00,966
I've been captured but don't worry,
Rose and Pete are still out there.

419
00:30:01,049 --> 00:30:04,344
They can rescue me.
Oh, well, never mind. You okay?

420
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:05,637
Yeah.

421
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:08,181
But they got Jackie.

422
00:30:08,265 --> 00:30:10,642
We were too late. Lumic killed her.

423
00:30:10,726 --> 00:30:13,979
And where is he? The famous Mr Lumic?

424
00:30:14,521 --> 00:30:16,940
Don't we get the chance to meet
our lord and master?

425
00:30:17,024 --> 00:30:19,067
He has been upgraded.

426
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:22,904
-So he's just like you?
-He is superior.

427
00:30:22,988 --> 00:30:27,534
The Lumic unit has been designated
Cyber controller.

428
00:30:37,210 --> 00:30:42,090
This is the Age of Steel and I am its creator.

429
00:30:47,596 --> 00:30:49,181
I'm almost there.

430
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:51,641
Not bad work.

431
00:30:57,356 --> 00:30:58,940
It's moving!

432
00:31:00,150 --> 00:31:01,651
You said it was dead!

433
00:31:01,735 --> 00:31:04,321
A robot suit's still a good robot. Wait a minute.

434
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:06,073
Hey, Cyberman. Over here.

435
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:10,619
Come on, you brainless lump of metal.

436
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:12,579
Come and have a go.

437
00:31:20,754 --> 00:31:22,422
(LOUD BEEPING)

438
00:31:23,799 --> 00:31:24,966
WOMAN: Oh, no!

439
00:31:28,261 --> 00:31:30,180
The transmitter is down!

440
00:31:30,514 --> 00:31:31,973
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

441
00:31:41,233 --> 00:31:44,361
That's my friends at work. Good boys.

442
00:31:44,986 --> 00:31:47,739
Mr Lumic, I think that's a vote for free will.

443
00:31:47,823 --> 00:31:52,327
I have factories waiting on seven continents.

444
00:31:52,661 --> 00:31:54,913
If the Ear Pods have failed,

445
00:31:54,996 --> 00:31:59,334
then the Cybermen will take humanity by force.

446
00:32:00,335 --> 00:32:04,548
London has fallen, so shall the world.

447
00:32:05,507 --> 00:32:08,301
Hold on, I've logged on to Cyber Control.
They're alive.

448
00:32:08,385 --> 00:32:10,429
The Doctor and Rose. There they are.

449
00:32:10,512 --> 00:32:15,392
-Never mind them, what the hell is that thing?
-Shh! Has this thing got sound?

450
00:32:15,475 --> 00:32:18,562
I will bring peace to the world.

451
00:32:18,645 --> 00:32:20,814
Everlasting peace

452
00:32:20,897 --> 00:32:23,984
and unity and uniformity.

453
00:32:24,526 --> 00:32:28,363
And imagination? What about that?
The one thing that led you here.

454
00:32:28,447 --> 00:32:30,740
Imagination, you're killing it dead.

455
00:32:31,408 --> 00:32:33,910
-What is your name?
-I'm the Doctor.

456
00:32:33,994 --> 00:32:37,456
A redundant title. Doctors need not exist.

457
00:32:37,539 --> 00:32:39,332
Cybermen never sicken.

458
00:32:39,416 --> 00:32:42,794
Yeah, but that's it. That's exactly the point.

459
00:32:43,128 --> 00:32:48,133
Oh, Lumic, you're a clever man.
I'd call you a genius except I'm in the room.

460
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:50,719
But everything you've invented,
you did to fight your sickness,

461
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:53,597
and that's brilliant, that is so human.

462
00:32:54,306 --> 00:32:56,766
But once you get rid of sickness and mortality,

463
00:32:56,850 --> 00:32:59,102
then what's there to strive for, eh?

464
00:32:59,769 --> 00:33:01,354
The Cybermen won't advance.

465
00:33:01,438 --> 00:33:03,315
You'll just stop.

466
00:33:03,398 --> 00:33:05,150
You'll stay like this forever.

467
00:33:05,233 --> 00:33:09,613
A metal Earth with metal men and metal thoughts,

468
00:33:09,696 --> 00:33:14,075
lacking the one thing
that makes this planet so alive. People!

469
00:33:14,618 --> 00:33:17,579
Ordinary, stupid, brilliant people.

470
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:20,957
You are proud of your emotions?

471
00:33:21,041 --> 00:33:22,417
Oh, yes.

472
00:33:22,501 --> 00:33:24,044
Then tell me, Doctor,

473
00:33:24,127 --> 00:33:28,298
have you known grief and rage and pain?

474
00:33:28,715 --> 00:33:30,592
Yes. Yes, I have.

475
00:33:30,884 --> 00:33:32,552
And they hurt?

476
00:33:32,636 --> 00:33:34,095
Oh, yes.

477
00:33:34,429 --> 00:33:38,141
I can set you free. Would you not want that?

478
00:33:38,225 --> 00:33:40,602
A life without pain?

479
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:42,521
You might as well kill me.

480
00:33:42,604 --> 00:33:45,398
Then I take that option.

481
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:47,442
It's not yours to take.

482
00:33:47,526 --> 00:33:48,944
You're a Cyber controller.

483
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:52,113
You don't control me
or anything with blood in its heart.

484
00:33:52,197 --> 00:33:54,824
You have no means of stopping me.

485
00:33:54,908 --> 00:33:58,578
I have an army. A species of my own.

486
00:33:59,371 --> 00:34:03,124
You just don't get it, do you? An army's nothing.

487
00:34:03,667 --> 00:34:08,463
'Cause those ordinary people, they're the key.
The most ordinary person can change the world.

488
00:34:08,630 --> 00:34:12,384
Some ordinary man or woman, some idiot.

489
00:34:12,509 --> 00:34:15,637
All it takes is for him to find,
say, the right numbers,

490
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:20,392
say, the right code, say, for example,
the code behind the emotional inhibitor.

491
00:34:20,475 --> 00:34:21,977
The code right in front of him.

492
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:25,605
'Cause even an idiot knows his computers
these days.

493
00:34:25,689 --> 00:34:29,484
Knows how to get past firewalls and passwords.

494
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:32,737
Knows how to find something encrypted
in the Lumic family database under,

495
00:34:32,821 --> 00:34:35,657
-what was it, Pete? Binary what?
-Binary 9.

496
00:34:35,782 --> 00:34:40,495
-Binary 9.
-An idiot could find that code. A cancellation code.

497
00:34:40,620 --> 00:34:44,124
And he'd keep on typing, keep on fighting,

498
00:34:44,207 --> 00:34:46,459
anything to save his friends.

499
00:34:46,543 --> 00:34:48,670
Your words are irrelevant.

500
00:34:49,462 --> 00:34:51,172
Talk too much, that's my problem.

501
00:34:51,256 --> 00:34:55,719
Lucky I got you that cheap tariff, Rose,
for all our long chats on your phone.

502
00:34:55,802 --> 00:34:56,970
The phone.

503
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:58,763
You will be deleted.

504
00:34:58,847 --> 00:35:02,142
Yes. Delete. Control. Hash.
All those lovely buttons.

505
00:35:02,225 --> 00:35:04,644
Then, of course, my particular favourite. Send.

506
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:08,898
And let's not forget how you seduced
all those ordinary people in the first place,

507
00:35:08,982 --> 00:35:11,651
by making every bit of technology
compatible with everything else.

508
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:12,986
It's for you.

509
00:35:13,612 --> 00:35:14,779
Like this.

510
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:17,532
(SCREAMING)

511
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:26,541
Yes!

512
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:33,048
(ALARM BLARING)

513
00:35:34,633 --> 00:35:36,259
(MOANING)

514
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,055
I'm sorry.

515
00:35:48,355 --> 00:35:50,231
What have you done?

516
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:52,734
I gave them back their souls.

517
00:35:52,817 --> 00:35:56,154
They can see what you've done, Lumic,
and it's killing them.

518
00:35:56,237 --> 00:35:58,031
Delete! Delete!

519
00:35:59,074 --> 00:36:00,075
Delete!

520
00:36:00,742 --> 00:36:02,077
(LUMIC SCREAMING)

521
00:36:16,049 --> 00:36:17,258
There's no way out.

522
00:36:18,385 --> 00:36:20,095
-What are you doing?
-We've got to get away.

523
00:36:20,178 --> 00:36:22,347
If that factory blows up,
this balloon's gonna ignite.

524
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:24,307
-Take it back!
-Mickey, they've had it.

525
00:36:24,432 --> 00:36:26,559
I said take it back!

526
00:36:28,895 --> 00:36:31,314
We're not leaving them behind.

527
00:36:31,398 --> 00:36:33,942
There's no way we're leaving them behind.

528
00:36:41,449 --> 00:36:42,701
Hold it.

529
00:36:44,411 --> 00:36:47,163
Rose? Rose, can you hear me? Head for the roof.

530
00:36:47,247 --> 00:36:49,749
It's Mickey. He says head for the roof.

531
00:37:03,638 --> 00:37:05,223
(GROANING)

532
00:37:07,851 --> 00:37:11,896
No!

533
00:37:22,031 --> 00:37:24,701
Mickey, where did you learn to fly that thing?

534
00:37:24,784 --> 00:37:28,288
PlayStation. Just hold on, Rose.
I'm coming to get you.

535
00:37:37,839 --> 00:37:40,341
-You can't go any lower.
-I've got to, man.

536
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:42,802
You're gonna crush them.

537
00:37:42,886 --> 00:37:45,638
There's gotta be something, there's got to be.

538
00:37:45,847 --> 00:37:47,140
Oh, yes.

539
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:53,521
You've got to be kidding.

540
00:37:53,605 --> 00:37:55,607
Rose, get on!

541
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:01,029
Hold on tight, we're going up.

542
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:05,283
Welcome to Mickey Smith Airlines.
Please enjoy your flight.

543
00:38:05,366 --> 00:38:06,826
(WHOOPING)

544
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:16,711
We did it! Mickey did it!

545
00:38:40,902 --> 00:38:43,738
Pete! Take this!

546
00:38:45,406 --> 00:38:46,658
Use it!

547
00:38:46,950 --> 00:38:50,995
Hold the button down.
Press it against the rope. Just do it!

548
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:57,418
Jackie Tyler. This is for her.

549
00:39:10,139 --> 00:39:11,933
(SCREAMING)

550
00:39:54,017 --> 00:39:56,060
So what happens inside that thing, then?

551
00:39:56,144 --> 00:39:57,770
Do you want to see?

552
00:39:57,854 --> 00:39:59,480
I don't think so.

553
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:06,696
But you two, you know, all that stuff you said
about different worlds.

554
00:40:08,615 --> 00:40:09,949
Who are you?

555
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:14,579
It's like you said.

556
00:40:14,662 --> 00:40:17,790
Imagine there are different worlds.

557
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:20,418
Parallel worlds.

558
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:23,796
Worlds with another Pete Tyler

559
00:40:25,214 --> 00:40:27,675
and Jackie Tyler is still alive.

560
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:29,802
And their daughter.

561
00:40:33,348 --> 00:40:35,725
-I've got to go.
-But if you just look inside...

562
00:40:35,808 --> 00:40:41,439
I can't. There's all those Lumic factories out there,
all those Cybermen still in storage.

563
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:43,775
Someone's got to tell the authorities
what happened.

564
00:40:43,858 --> 00:40:45,693
Carry on the fight.

565
00:40:47,028 --> 00:40:48,404
Rose.

566
00:40:48,821 --> 00:40:51,074
I've only got five minutes of power.

567
00:40:51,366 --> 00:40:53,284
-We've got to go.
-The Doctor could show you how.

568
00:40:53,368 --> 00:40:55,495
Thank you for everything.

569
00:40:57,205 --> 00:40:58,414
Dad...

570
00:41:00,708 --> 00:41:02,669
Don't. Just don't.

571
00:41:18,768 --> 00:41:20,269
MICKEY: Here it is.

572
00:41:21,688 --> 00:41:24,399
I found it. Not a crease.

573
00:41:24,565 --> 00:41:27,568
My suit. Good man.

574
00:41:27,902 --> 00:41:30,738
Now then, Jake, we've got to run,
but one more thing.

575
00:41:30,822 --> 00:41:34,200
Mrs Moore, her real name was Angela Price.

576
00:41:34,617 --> 00:41:38,287
She's got a husband out there and children.
Find them.

577
00:41:38,371 --> 00:41:40,999
Tell them how she died saving the world.

578
00:41:41,082 --> 00:41:42,917
Yeah, course I will.

579
00:41:43,001 --> 00:41:44,377
Off we go, then.

580
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:46,212
Erm...

581
00:41:46,295 --> 00:41:48,131
Thing is, I'm staying.

582
00:41:48,631 --> 00:41:51,134
You're doing what?

583
00:41:51,217 --> 00:41:52,635
You can't.

584
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:56,764
It sort of balances out
'cause this world lost its Ricky, but there's me.

585
00:41:57,223 --> 00:42:00,893
And there's work to be done
with all those Cybermen still out there.

586
00:42:00,977 --> 00:42:02,895
But you can't stay.

587
00:42:04,147 --> 00:42:06,107
Rose, my gran's here.

588
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:09,944
She's still alive. My old gran, remember her?

589
00:42:10,028 --> 00:42:11,112
Yeah.

590
00:42:11,237 --> 00:42:12,739
She needs me.

591
00:42:13,781 --> 00:42:16,325
What about me? What if I need you?

592
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,412
Yeah, but Rose, you don't.

593
00:42:21,164 --> 00:42:23,249
It's just you and him, isn't it?

594
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:29,797
We had something a long time ago,
but not anymore.

595
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:33,426
Well, we'll come back.

596
00:42:33,509 --> 00:42:36,054
We can travel anywhere. Come and see you, yeah?

597
00:42:36,137 --> 00:42:37,430
We can't.

598
00:42:39,807 --> 00:42:43,144
I told you, travel between parallel worlds
is impossible.

599
00:42:43,811 --> 00:42:45,188
We only got here by accident.

600
00:42:45,271 --> 00:42:49,400
We fell through a crack in time.
When we leave, I've got to close it.

601
00:42:51,861 --> 00:42:53,613
We can't ever return.

602
00:43:00,161 --> 00:43:01,370
Doctor.

603
00:43:02,830 --> 00:43:06,000
Take Rose's phone. It's got the code.
Get it out there.

604
00:43:06,667 --> 00:43:08,669
Stop those factories.

605
00:43:11,214 --> 00:43:12,340
Good luck.

606
00:43:14,342 --> 00:43:15,760
Mickey the idiot.

607
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:17,178
Watch it.

608
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:32,443
Thanks.

609
00:43:34,570 --> 00:43:37,156
We've had a laugh, though, haven't we?

610
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,617
Seen it all, been there and back.

611
00:43:42,453 --> 00:43:44,580
Who'd have thought, me and you,
off that old estate,

612
00:43:44,664 --> 00:43:46,582
flying through the stars.

613
00:43:46,707 --> 00:43:49,418
All those years, just sitting there...

614
00:43:50,837 --> 00:43:52,922
imagining what we'd do one day.

615
00:43:55,091 --> 00:43:57,218
We never saw this, did we?

616
00:44:05,393 --> 00:44:07,395
Go on. Don't miss your flight.

617
00:44:34,755 --> 00:44:36,674
Jake, you want to watch this.

618
00:44:42,305 --> 00:44:44,182
JAKE: What the hell?

619
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:47,310
MICKEY: That's the Doctor in the Tardis.

620
00:44:48,269 --> 00:44:49,645
With Rose Tyler.

621
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:01,365
(WHOOSHING)

622
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:09,123
You're alive. Oh, Mum, you're alive.

623
00:45:09,749 --> 00:45:12,126
Well, I was the last time I looked.

624
00:45:12,585 --> 00:45:14,879
What is it? What's happened, sweetheart?

625
00:45:14,962 --> 00:45:16,839
What's wrong? Where did you go?

626
00:45:16,964 --> 00:45:18,591
Far away.

627
00:45:19,467 --> 00:45:22,136
That was far away.

628
00:45:22,511 --> 00:45:23,804
Where's Mickey?

629
00:45:23,888 --> 00:45:25,264
He's gone home.

630
00:45:38,778 --> 00:45:42,073
I know it's not easy
with my face looking exactly like Ricky,

631
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:45,034
but I'm a different man, I'm not replacing him.

632
00:45:45,117 --> 00:45:48,412
But we can remember him by fighting in his name.

633
00:45:49,997 --> 00:45:54,085
With all those cyber factories out there,
do you think there'd be one in Paris?

634
00:45:54,168 --> 00:45:56,754
-Yeah.
-Then let's go and liberate Paris.

635
00:45:56,837 --> 00:45:59,340
What, you and me? In a van?

636
00:46:00,383 --> 00:46:02,385
There's nothing wrong with a van.

637
00:46:02,468 --> 00:46:05,596
I once saved the universe with a big yellow truck.

638
00:46:26,909 --> 00:46:30,329
There you go, sir.
All wired up for the great occasion.

639
00:46:30,788 --> 00:46:32,707
WOMAN: Someone help me, please!

640
00:46:32,832 --> 00:46:36,085
It's happening all over the place.
They're turning into monsters.

641
00:46:40,673 --> 00:46:43,342
ROSE: Ordinary people
are being struck down and changed

642
00:46:43,426 --> 00:46:46,137
and the only new thing in the house
is a television.

643
00:46:46,554 --> 00:46:52,059
Men in black? Vanishing police cars?
This is Churchill's England, not Stalin's Russia.

644
00:46:52,143 --> 00:46:54,270
Are you sitting comfortably?

645
00:46:54,395 --> 00:46:55,896
Good.

646
00:46:55,980 --> 00:46:57,732
Then we'll begin.

